gomodel:SYNGO_319  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using a newly produced monoclonal antibody to TI-VAMP that improves signal/noise immunodetection, authors reported that TI-VAMP is also present in subsets of axon terminals of the adult rat brain.\n\nFour distinctive populations of labelled axon terminals were identified. The presynaptic localisation of TI-VAMP in these locations was demonstrated by co-localisation with synaptophysin.\n\n1) The hippocampal mossy fibres of the dentate gyrus and of CA3 (Fig 3A-C).\n2) The striatal peridendritic terminal plexuses in the globus pallidus (GP), substantia nigra pars reticulata (SNr),\n3) peridendritic plexuses in the central nucleus of the amygdala\n4) The primary sensory afferents in the dorsal horn of the spinal cord (Fig 5D-E).\n\nSubcellular localisation of TI-VAMP:\nAuthors carried out ultrastructural investigations, focussing on the hippocampal dendritic and axon terminal TI-VAMP labelled. The preparations were analysed with two types of pre-embedding procedures (immunogold and immunoperoxidase) on adult rat brain samples. In the hilus and in CA3,TI-VAMP labelling was distributed throughout the terminal bouton and, at their level of resolution, it decorated indiscriminately all the synaptic vesicles (Fig 6).\n\nFinally author showed that TI-VAMP is not restricted to one neurotransmitter, TI-VAMP is present in both GABAergic and glutamatergic terminals (Fig 8). Experimental description: Adult (200 g) Sprague-Dawley rats were anaesthetised, and kept 2h at 4 °C before dissecting the brains. Vibratome sections (50 um thick) through the primary somatosensory cortex and the hippocampus were collected.\n\nAntibody production: Female Biozzi BP2 mice were immunised by i.p. injection of 40 ug of the recombinant domain of TI-VAMP." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_319" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

